column6: pdt_description
Made with orange freshly grown and harvested at prime growing season
Made with fresh strawberries from Hokkaido
Using freshly squeezed lemons, the ganache filling of this macaron consists of jam, lemon juice and cream.
For all-time chocolate lovers, you will want to know this macaron's ganache is mixed with lots of 65% dark chocolate goodness!
Artificially colored blue, this chap's striking color will not make you regret its exquisite flavour! Note: chewy candies included in ganache.
Made with the ever popular milo drink powder, added with frosted icing as the confectionery center filling.
With the coloring of its sandwich cookies naturally derived from berries, Mixed Berries Delight is a sure hit with people who love berries.
With its luxuriously red meringue cookies, the Red Velvet is a popular flavour choice for those looking to gift dear ones.
An exotic shade of yellow gold gives this flavour a mysterious aura of the untried and untasted. If you love tropical climate and tropical fruits, do give it a go!
Definitely for the mango lovers, there is so much fresh mango pulp inside the ganache, you will hardly notice the cream in its filling!
Giving salted caramel an extra burst of flavour, coffee is added in, to the joy of those who love coffee as well!
The royal mixture of dark chocolate, cherries and berries that make up this classic flavour will give you a run for your money!

Anticipate the burst of passionfruit goodness from this exotic flavour found none other than here!
A classic citrus flavour from a long time ago, you will not be disappointed with our shop's version!
A tangy delectable sour tinge is always good in a dessert for after meals! Just imagine the lack of zest!
The all original dark chocolate everyone knows about.
Don't be guilty to try out a little rum once in a while! This rum bonbon mixed with chocolate and cherries will leave you craving for more.
Infused with white tea with berries thrown into the mix, this bonbon is a sure hit amongst tea lovers.
No longer a seasonal specialty flavour, be sure to try this out whenever you feel a twang of longing to see cherry blossoms!
Another popular recommendation for tea lovers, black tea now comes with a fruity pal: mango. Don't miss this fruit and tea combination!
Another flavour with a unique twist to the classic cookies and cream. This time, coffee decides to be the other half!
The only white chocolate flavour amongst all bonbons, don't underestimate its uniqueness! It comes together marvelously well with fresh rose petals.
Salted caramel is never a lonely solo flavour again, with the companionship of coffee.
Never forget the original classic of dark chocolate with berries.

A slice of cake full of salted caramel goodness, for you or your loved one!
A tri-layered cake consisting of chocolate, strawberry, and vanilla. Enjoy the mixture of different flavours in one cake!
Finished with a dollop of fresh lemon marmalade, the baked lemon crust of the cake crumble under the spoon to reveal a filling of layered lemon delight!
Made with care with 65% dark chocolate, and dark chocolate fudge, chocolate lovers will love this.
Infused with sakura flavored tea, the vanilla chiffon cake is also topped and layered with sakura essence buttercream.
The velvety red cake with vanilla cream and cherries gives an enticing impression.
Baked fresh daily with matcha powder imported from Japan, the mont blanc is worth trying!
The citrusy taste of the lemon used in the meringue enhances the sweetness and fluffiness of it.
Mango and passionfruit are the best of tropical fruits combination there can be for just a tart.
If you like cheese, the gentle subtle taste of the blackberries will bring out the flavours of the cheesecake tart.
The pistachios and strawberries go so well together, you won't believe it!
Topped with fresh strawberries atop strawberry sauce and gelatin, the cheesecake and crispy base crust combination shall not disappoint anyone.
